### The Geometry of Shrinkage

We now have three distinct sets of inferences:
* No Pooling: The raw, isolated estimates (highly vulnerable to the noise of low $N_j$).
* Complete Pooling: The rigid, universal average (blind to genuine individual differences).
* Partial Pooling: Our hierarchical NCP model estimates (the precision-weighted Bayesian compromise).

To truly evaluate the epistemological value of these models, we must plot them not just against each other, but against the True Generative Parameters (the hidden reality we simulated in R). We will also extract the naive arithmetic mean of the No Pooling estimates to contrast it with the precision-weighted Partial Pooling mean.

